 HOURS ON 7/31/08 TWO EMPTY RAILCARS, CR 238272 AND NS 486748, ROLLED UNDER THEIR OWN POWER DOWN THE LEAD INTO NUMBER 1712 TRACK AND INTO R-6 STICKING THE BUMPING POST AND THE CEMENT WALL JUST BEHIND IT.  THE CAR DAMAGED THE BUMPING POST BEYOND REPAIR, DAMAGED THE CEMENT WALL AND STRUCK THE ASSEMBLY PLANTS FRAMING TO THE CHAIN THAT DRIVES THE PLANTS ASSEMBLY LINE CAUSING THE PLANT TO SHUT DOWN. \r\n\r\nI WITH THE HELP OF EMPLOYEE FROM PROGRESSIVE RAIL, THE CONDUCTOR AND YARDMASTER AS THE ENGINEER PERFORMED A REENACTMENT OF THE EVENT, FROM 2330 TO 0015 HRS, ON THE SAME TRACK WITH THE SAME CONDUCTOR AND THE SAME TWO CARS. THE CONCLUSION WAS THAT THE HAND BRAKE ON THE NS 486748WOULD NOT HOLD THE TWO EMPTY CARS FROM THE SPOT IN WHICH THEY WERE CUT OFF FROM.  THE HAND BRAKE ONTHE NS 486748 INDEED HAD A MECHANICAL FAILURE.    \r\n\r\nAT 0815 HRS ON 8/1/08 THE CHIEF INSPECTOR ANDMECHANICAL INSPECTOR FROM THE FRA ARRIVED AT MVP.  THEY INSPECTED THE CARS AND THE MECHANICAL INSPECTOR FOUND THAT NOT ONLY WAS THE HAND BRAKE ON THE NS 468748 WAS INEFFECTIVE BUT THAT THE SLACK ADJUSTER WAS NOT OPERATING AS INTENDED.  HE STATED \"THAT THERE WAS NO WAY THE AIR OR HAND BRAKE WOULD HAVE HELD THE TWO CARS\".\r\n\r\nBETWEEN 1300 AND 1400 HRS A SECOND REENACTMENT WAS PERFORMED BY MVP AND THE FRA TO FIND THE ROOT CAUSE OF THE INCIDENT. THE RESULTS OF BOTH REENACTMENTS WERE CONCLUSIVE, MECHANICAL FAILURE WAS THE CAUSE FOR THE INCIDENT.","Joint Track Type":"Industry","Joint Track Class":"X","Class Code":"3","Class":"3","Joint CD":"1","Incident Key":"MVP73108200807","Report Key":"MVP73108200807","Reporting Railroad Company Grouping":"","Reporting Railroad Class":"Class 3","Reporting Railroad SMT Grouping":"","Reporting Parent Railroad Company Code":"MVP","Reporting Parent Railroad Company Name":"Missouri & Valley Park Railroad Corp","Reporting Railroad Holding Company":"Not Assigned","Other Railroad Company Grouping":"","Other Railroad Class":"","Other Railroad SMT Grouping":"","Other Paren